ving%20before%20completing%20one%20year%20because%20I%20felt%20there%20were%20problems%20at%20the%20company%2C%20and%20I%20realized%20I'd%20chased%20a%20title%20instead%20of%20thinking%20things%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20advanced%20in%20my%20career%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20needed%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20skills%20I%20needed%20to%20acquire%20rather%20than%20the%20prestige%20of%20a%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20joined%20Kiva%2C%20a%20microfinance%20nonprofit%2C%20in%202018%2C%20I%20didn't%20view%20it%20as%20a%20permanent%20job.%20I%20took%20the%20job%20to%20gain%20skills%20outside%20a%20product%20and%20engineering%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20time%20there%2C%20I%20learned%20about%20business%20development%20and%20communicated%20with%20UN%20officials%20and%20central%20bank%20leaders.%20Not%20only%20did%20I%20get%20to%20experience%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20other%20teams%2C%20but%20I%20also%20got%20to%20know%20different%20contours%20of%20the%20product%2C%20business%2C%20and%20customer%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20moved%20into%20my%20next%20role%2C%20a%20general%20manager%20at%20the%20communications%20company%20Twilio%2C%20I%20had%20a%20broader%20scope%20of%20experience%20and%20could%20operate%20more%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20accelerate%20quickly%20into%20a%20senior%20role%2C%20but%20taking%20a%20less%20fancy%20role%20and%20diversifying%20your%20experience%20might%20mean%20your%20upside%20long-term%20is%20much%20higher.%20If%20you're%20thinking%20two%20jobs%20ahead%2C%20evaluate%20what%20opportunities%20will%20help%20you%20more%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20It's%20a%20marathon%2C%20not%20a%20sprint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f8b3213d-3c39-4d8a-83cb-04c2300c28bd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMistake%202%3A%20Not%20investing%20in%20relationships%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%20my%20career%2C%20because%20I%20didn't%20know%20how%20corporations%20worked%2C%20it%20was%20easy%20to%20think%20that%20everyone%20in%20a%20company%20was%20aligned%20and%20felt%20the%20same%20way%2C%20which%20is%20foolish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-quit-working-twitter-elon-musk-takeover-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworked%20at%20Twitter%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20their%20growth%20team%2C%20my%20job%20was%20to%20play%20in%20other%20people's%20sandboxes%20and%20tweak%20things.%20The%20company%20was%20having%20a%20difficult%20growth%20time%2C%20and%20we%20had%20to%20be%20hyper-focused%20on%20hitting%20our%20OKRs.%20This%20sometimes%20came%20at%20the%20detriment%20of%20my%20team's%20relationship%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20product%20engineering%20org.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20to%20step%20into%20other%20team's%20territories%20and%20move%20quickly.%20I%20felt%20I%20needed%20to%20hit%20a%20goal%20at%20all%20costs%2C%20and%20the%20problem%20was%20%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3Eat%20all%20costs.%26quot%3B%20We%20often%20weren't%20on%20the%20same%20page%20as%20that%20team%20and%20had%20to%20go%20back%20and%20repair%20relationships%20afterward.%20In%20hindsight%2C%20I%20needed%20to%20do%20a%20better%20job%20of%20explaining%20why%20we%20were%20doing%20something%20from%20the%20outset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20is%20trying%20to%20achieve%20a%20company's%20mission%20in%20the%20same%20way%2C%20and%20so%20by%20investing%20in%20relationships%2C%20you%20can%20more%20clearly%20communicate%20how%20you%20align%20with%20others%20in%20a%20company.%20Even%20if%20they%20don't%20align%20with%20you%2C%20they'll%20respect%20your%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223ae2edfb-9210-4043-b76d-5c25b53f27a0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMistake%203%3A%20Over-emulating%20senior%20leaders%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%20my%20career%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20role%20model%20in%20the%20corporate%20environment%2C%20so%20I%20questioned%20what%20%26quot%3Bgood%26quot%3B%20looked%20like%20and%20how%20I%20should%20show%20up.%3C%2Fp%3